\dfrac1{1-2x} = 1 + (2x) + (2x)^2 + (2x)^3 + (2x)^4 + (2x)^5 + (2x)^6 + \cdots = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} 2^kx^k
\dfrac{d}{dx} \left(\dfrac1{1-2x} \right)= \dfrac2{\left(1-2x \right)^2} = \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} k2^k x^{k-1}
\dfrac1{\left(1-2x \right)^2} = \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} k2^{k-1} x^{k-1}
